  "texts": [
    "Instructions for replicating this example are available in the repository's documentation [62].This example discusses text-to-image tasks, where traits are explicitly included inside the prompt using reserved keywords.",
    "Models supporting text-to-text tasks such as GPT-4, Gemini or Claude do not typically support reserved keywords inside the prompt.",
    "Some models like Mistralfoot_0 have reserved control tokens but they are filtered during the parsing of the prompt for security reasons, to avoid injection attacks.",
    "Nevertheless, it is still possible to customize the output of the prompt in several ways:• Using delimiters to separate different sections of the prompt: Prompt engineering guides for several language models suggest the use of different delimiters to separate different sections of a prompt.",
    "For example, Claudefoot_1 strongly suggests the use of XML tags; GPT 3 proposes the use of triple quotation marks, XML tags or section titles; Mistralfoot_3 suggests the use of separators like ### or <<<>>>."
  ],
